You sent an attachment.
This illusion is known as the flashed face distortion effect, a phenomenon where normal faces start to appear grotesque or monstrous when viewed in quick succession while focusing on a fixed point. By keeping your eyes on the red dot, your brain begins to exaggerate differences between the faceslike uneven features, asymmetry, or unusual proportionsturning them into distorted, almost caricature-like versions of themselves. The effect happens because our visual system processes changes relative to what were fixating on. Instead of seeing each face as it is, our brains amplify contrasts between them, making perfectly normal faces look warped. Its a striking example of how perception doesnt always reflect reality, and how easily the human mind can be tricked by context and focus.
